          <!-- ── AI Use Policy ── -->
          <h3>AI Use &mdash; Mahi Mode Level 2 (Tīmata ki AI)</h3>

          <p>
            This assessment is set at <strong>Mahi Mode Level 2 &mdash; To Start (Tīmata ki AI)</strong>.
            AI is a research and learning tool here, not a writer. <strong>All written work
            must be your own.</strong>
          </p>

          <div class="ai-split">

            <div class="ai-split__allowed">
              <h4>AI <em>is</em> permitted for</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Researching and understanding biological concepts</li>
                <li>Brainstorming and organising your ideas before you write</li>
                <li>Checking your understanding of a process or a definition</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="ai-split__not-allowed">
              <h4>AI is <em>NOT</em> permitted for</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Writing any part of your report. All written content must be in your own words.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

          </div>

          <h4>What This Looks Like in Practice &mdash; Using Glucose Homeostasis as the Example</h4>

          <p>
            You already know the glucose system from the dry run. Here's how AI use would
            have looked on that task, as a pattern for your actual internal:
          </p>

          <div class="ai-examples">

            <div class="ai-example ai-example--ok">
              <div class="ai-example__tag">OK</div>
              <p class="ai-example__prompt">&ldquo;Explain how insulin triggers GLUT4 translocation in muscle cells.&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="ai-example__why">
                Research. You use the output to build your own understanding, then write the
                explanation in Part B in your own words.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="ai-example ai-example--ok">
              <div class="ai-example__tag">OK</div>
              <p class="ai-example__prompt">&ldquo;What are the key components of the glucose negative feedback loop? Give me a checklist I can use to plan Part A.&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="ai-example__why">
                Brainstorming and organising ideas. You use the checklist to structure your
                own notes, then write Part A yourself.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="ai-example ai-example--ok">
              <div class="ai-example__tag">OK</div>
              <p class="ai-example__prompt">&ldquo;Is it correct to say glucagon targets hepatocytes via a G-protein coupled receptor that activates adenylyl cyclase?&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="ai-example__why">
                Checking understanding. You verify a fact and then explain the mechanism in
                your own words.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="ai-example ai-example--not-ok">
              <div class="ai-example__tag ai-example__tag--bad">NOT OK</div>
              <p class="ai-example__prompt">&ldquo;Write me a 300-word explanation of the glucose feedback loop for Part B of my NCEA Level 3 Biology internal.&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="ai-example__why">
                AI is writing your assessment for you. Not permitted. Even if you &ldquo;edit&rdquo;
                the output, the thinking and the sentence structure aren't yours.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="ai-example ai-example--not-ok">
              <div class="ai-example__tag ai-example__tag--bad">NOT OK</div>
              <p class="ai-example__prompt">&ldquo;Rewrite this paragraph I wrote so it sounds more like Excellence-level writing.&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="ai-example__why">
                AI is producing your written content, just downstream of your draft. The
                voice, vocabulary, and connecting logic stop being yours. Not permitted.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="ai-example ai-example--not-ok">
              <div class="ai-example__tag ai-example__tag--bad">NOT OK</div>
              <p class="ai-example__prompt">&ldquo;Give me three Excellence points about the biochemistry of glucose regulation that I can paste into Part D.&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="ai-example__why">
                AI is supplying the specific arguments. Research to <em>understand</em>, not
                to <em>harvest</em>. The Excellence thinking must be yours.
              </p>
            </div>

          </div>

          <div class="connection-box">
            <h4>The RAS Check &mdash; Before You Use Any AI Output</h4>
            <p>
              <strong>R</strong>elevance &mdash; did it actually answer the question, and is
              it appropriate for this task?<br/>
              <strong>A</strong>ccuracy &mdash; have you verified facts, stats, and sources
              against the textbook or your class notes?<br/>
              <strong>S</strong>afety &mdash; is the output appropriate and unbiased, and did
              you leave personal information out of the prompt?<br/>
              <strong>R</strong>ewriting &mdash; have you rewritten the content in your own
              words and voice before including it?
            </p>
          </div>

