              is an Academic Authenticity breach at MBC and may be treated as dishonest
              conduct. A signed declaration doesn't guarantee the use was appropriate
              &mdash; authenticity checks (milestone conversations, draft review, oral
              questioning) decide that.
            </div>
          </div>


          <!-- ── Authenticity ── -->
          <h3>Authenticity Milestone Checks</h3>

          <p>
            There are four authenticity milestones on this assessment. These are short
            conversations about your progress, not tests &mdash; their job is to verify the
            work is yours. Missing them can lead to disqualification from the standard. All
            checks are recorded. The first one is this week (see Lessons 2 &amp; 3 below).
          </p>

        </section>


