              <strong>Apologies, team &mdash; I got this one wrong.</strong> I thought the
              textbook site would work with your school email. It doesn't. The NotebookLM
              sharing permissions on our school Google tenant are locking you out.
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            <strong>The workaround:</strong> use a <strong>non-school email address</strong>
            to open the textbook site. A personal Google account works best (if you don't
            already have one, signing up is free and takes about two minutes at
            <a href="https://accounts.google.com/signup" target="_blank" rel="noopener">accounts.google.com/signup</a>).
          </p>

          <ol class="step-list">
            <li>Sign in to Chrome or a browser tab with your <strong>personal</strong> Google account (not your @mbc.school.nz account).</li>
            <li>Open the <a href={textbookSiteUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">textbook site</a>.</li>
            <li>When prompted to request access, send the request from your personal account. I'll approve it as soon as I see it come through.</li>
            <li>Once you're in, you can ask it questions about the content, get summaries, and generate study aids.</li>
          </ol>

          <p>
            If you hit a wall, flag it to Ms Dow and move on &mdash; don't burn writing time
            on access problems. Week 10 and Week 9 on this site cover the same material.
          </p>


